{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"timeoutAdd"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"interval"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"function"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GSourceFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The given "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"function"},{"type":"text","text":" is called repeatedly until it returns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[const"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove"},{"type":"text","text":"] or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", at which point the timeout is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"automatically destroyed and the function will not be called again. The first"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call to the function will be at the end of the first "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that timeout functions may be delayed, due to the processing of other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"event sources. Thus they should not be relied on for precise timing."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After each call to the timeout function, the time of the next"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"timeout is recalculated based on the current time and the given interval"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(it does not try to ‘catch up’ time lost in delays)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources"},{"type":"text","text":" for details"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"data"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to have a timer in the “seconds” range and do not care"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"about the exact time of the first call of the timer, use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add_seconds"},{"type":"text","text":"] function; this function allows for more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"optimizations and more efficient system power usage."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This internally creates a main loop source using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_source_new"},{"type":"text","text":"] and attaches it to the global"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"] using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Source.attach"},{"type":"text","text":"], so the callback"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be invoked in whichever thread is running that main context. You can do"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these steps manually